of inquiry, and be allowed full access to, and furnished copies of, records relevant to his case at all stages of proceeding, prior to repeal by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/513/tII/s213"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–513, title II, § 213","children":[],"tail":", title VII, § 701, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-12-12"},"text":"Dec. 12, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/2885"},"text":"94 Stat. 2885","children":[],"tail":", 2955, effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-09-15"},"text":"Sept. 15, 1981","children":[],"tail":". See "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1185"},"text":"section 1185 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idaa39ee74-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2021—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s1833"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, § 1833","children":[],"tail":"("},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":")(1), (2), redesignated subsec. (g) of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2321"},"text":"section 2321 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as subsec. (a) of this section, substituted “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s3782/c"},"text":"section 3782(c) of this title","children":[],"tail":"” for “subsection (d)(3)” in two places, and realigned margins of pars. (1) and (2). Amendment directing substitution of “(1) Upon failure” for “(1) Upon failure” as part of margin realignment was executed by substituting “(1) Upon failure” for “(1) Upon a failure” to reflect the probable intent of Congress."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s1833"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, § 1833","children":[],"tail":"("},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},